before.enText: not used in the progressive tenses

data.enText: if one thing includes another, it has the second thing as one of its parts

data.chText: 这次游览包括参观科学博物馆。
data.enText: The tour included a visit to the Science Museum.

data.chText: 这个价钱是否包括税款？
你的职责是打信件和接电话。
data.enText: Your duties include typing letters and answering the telephone.
to make sb/sth part of sth

data.chText: 你应该在文章里举一些例子。
data.enText: You should include some examples in your essay.

data.chText: 这个国家的代表都被列为会议的观察员。
data.enText: Representatives from the country were included as observers at the conference.

simple_means.memory_skill: in 向内；进入 + clud 关 + e → 关在里面 → 包括

ex.enText: This car can hold four people.
How much water does this bottle hold?

synonyms.bx: 指容纳某一数量的人或事物，强调包容的能力。

ex.enText: What is contained in the bottle?

ex.chText: 这个书架上现在有60本书，但它能装下150本。
ex.enText: This bookshelf currently contains 60 books but can hold 150 ones.

ex.chText: 这份报告包含你所需的一切数据。
ex.enText: This report contains all the data you need.

synonyms.bx: 指容器装有具体东西，含仍有剩余空间之意；也指包含具体之物或数据、信息等。

ex.chText: 这辆新车包含了许多改进。
ex.enText: The new car embodies many improvements.

ex.chText: 那项提案包含在决议草案中吗？
ex.enText: Has the proposal been embodied in that draft resolution?

synonyms.bx: 指包含某些内容，而这些内容是某事物的组成部分。

ex.chText: 自然科学包括许多学科。
该理论涉及心理学的不同方面。
ex.enText: This theory embraces different aspects of psychology.

synonyms.bx: 指包含和整体有关的细节。

ex.chText: 她的作品包括小说和散文。
ex.enText: Her writings include novels and prose.

synonyms.bx: 指包括属于整体的部分，可以是具体的或抽象的。

ex.chText: 新员工们需要知道这份工作包括什么。
ex.enText: New employees need to know what the job will involve.

ex.chText: 考试将包括朗读一则新闻。
ex.enText: The test will involve reading a piece of news.

ex.chText: 她没想到写一部小说需要做这么多的工作。
ex.enText: She didn't realize writing a novel involved so much work.

synonyms.bx: 指必然包括某种结果，所接的事物通常是抽象的。

tr: add as part of something else
put in as part of a set, group, or category
example: We must include this chemical element in the group
I include you in the list of culprits

tr: allow participation in or the right to be part of
permit to exercise the rights, functions, and responsibilities of
example: She was admitted to the New Jersey Bar

tr: have as a part, be made up out of
example: The list includes the names of many famous writers

value.def: If one thing includes another thing, it has the other thing as one of its parts.

example.ex: A good British breakfast always includes sausages...
example.tran: 一顿丰盛的英式早餐总会包括香肠。

example.ex: The trip has been extended to include a few other events...
example.tran: 旅程被延长，其他几项活动也被包括进来。

example.ex: The list includes many British internationals.
example.tran: 名单中包括了许多英国国际级选手。

value.def: If someone or something is included in a large group, system, or area, they become a part of it or are considered a part of it.

example.ex: I had worked hard to be included in a project like this...
example.tran: 为参与这样的项目,我过去一直努力工作。

example.ex: The President is expected to include this idea in his education plan.
example.tran: 人们期望总统把这一意见列入他的教育计划当中。

value.tran: 把…列为…的一部分;把…算入
